{
  "stem": "3820.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my grandfather David and the two-- Chaim and Sana, the two sons and the three daughters and their husbands and the children went.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went across the border at night by bribery.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I don't know how.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we wandered around in Russian-occupied Poland for a while.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we settled in a town, Zofjowka.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's where we lived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandfather and-- and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had taken some of the machines that they used in making the shoes with them so that they were able to set up a business of sorts to survive.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we lived there until the Germans marched in in 1941 and we found ourselves right back where we started.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that point, we were almost immediately put into a ghetto in the town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] we-- we lived like in a two-room place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember we had, I believe, one Passover there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember the women getting together and baking the matzas in one place, where they made it clean for Passover, and then distributing it to the houses.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was hanging from a-- in a sheet from the-- from the ceiling.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my uncle Chaim had always been-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] oh, I don't know, maybe a little wiser than a lot of us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And because the Germans made my grandfather make shoes for them, he was allowed to leave the ghetto to deliver them to their post or-- and he was-- when he was able to leave the ghetto, he made it a-- a point to learn as much as he could.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when there were rumblings of something happening, he-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he got part of our family out into the forests.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
